# 🏗️ Unified Activity System — Architecture & Implementation Plan

> **Project:** LifeLink Backend  
> **Stack:** Node.js (Express) · MongoDB (Mongoose) · Clean Architecture  
> **Target Consumer:** Flutter mobile app (Bloc pattern)  
> **Date:** 2026-05-04

---

## 1️⃣ High-Level Architecture

### Where Activity Fits

The Activity System is a **read-optimized, append-only event log** that sits as a **cross-cutting concern** alongside the existing Notification system. It does NOT replace notifications — it complements them.

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Existing Services"
        DS[donation.service]
        RS[reward.service]
        NS[notification.service]
        DC[donor.controller]
    end

    subgraph "New Activity Layer"
        AS[activity.service]
        AM[Activity Model]
        AC[activity.controller]
        AR[activity.routes]
    end

    DS -->|"onDonationCreated / onStatusChange"| AS
    RS -->|"onPointsAwarded / onRewardRedeemed"| AS
    DC -->|"onUrgentResponse / onProfileUpdate"| AS
    AS --> AM
    AC --> AS
    AR --> AC
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Activity ≠ Notification.** Notifications are actionable alerts (read/unread, TTL-expiring). Activities are a permanent historical record of what the user did. They serve different purposes and must remain separate collections.

### Responsibility Breakdown

| Layer | File | Responsibility |
|-------|------|----------------|
| **Model** | `Activity.model.js` | Schema definition, indexes, TTL policy, enum validation |
| **Service** | `activity.service.js` | Create activities, query timeline, deduplication logic, dashboard aggregation |
| **Controller** | `activity.controller.js` | HTTP request handling, input validation, response formatting via `response.js` |
| **Routes** | `activity.routes.js` | Endpoint definitions, auth middleware, rate limiting |

### Interaction with Existing Modules

The Activity service is a **consumer** — it is called BY other services, never the reverse. No existing service should ever depend on or import from the activity service for its core logic.

- **donation.service.js** → calls `activityService.logActivity()` after donation creation/completion
- **reward.service.js** → calls `activityService.logActivity()` after points award / reward redemption
- **donor.controller.js** → calls `activityService.logActivity()` after profile update, urgent request accept/decline
- **Activity never calls** donation, reward, or notification services

---

## 2️⃣ Data Modeling Plan

### Entity Structure

| Field | Type | Required | Purpose |
|-------|------|----------|---------|
| `userId` | ObjectId (ref: User) | ✅ | Owner of the activity — who performed the action |
| `type` | String (enum) | ✅ | Category discriminator: `donation`, `reward`, `emergency_response`, `profile_update` |
| `action` | String | ✅ | Human-readable verb: `"donated_blood"`, `"earned_points"`, `"redeemed_reward"`, `"accepted_urgent_request"`, `"declined_urgent_request"`, `"updated_profile"` |
| `title` | String (max 200) | ✅ | Display-ready title for the Flutter UI, e.g. `"Blood Donation Completed"` |
| `description` | String (max 500) | ✅ | Summary sentence, e.g. `"Donated 1 unit of A+ blood to Cairo Hospital"` |
| `referenceId` | String | ❌ | ID of the related entity (donationId, redemptionId, etc.) — used for deduplication and deep linking |
| `referenceType` | String (enum) | ❌ | Type of referenced entity: `Donation`, `PointsTransaction`, `RewardRedemption`, `Request`, `User` |
| `metadata` | Mixed (Object) | ❌ | Lightweight snapshot of key data at creation time (avoids JOIN-heavy reads) |
| `icon` | String | ❌ | Icon identifier for the Flutter UI (e.g. `"heart"`, `"trophy"`, `"flash"`, `"user"`) |
| `createdAt` | Date (auto) | ✅ | Timestamp — the timeline sort key |

### Field Reasoning

- **`userId`**: Scopes all queries. Every activity belongs to exactly one user.
- **`type`**: Enables filtering by category on the mobile app (tabs/chips).
- **`action`**: More granular than `type`. A single `type: "donation"` can have actions like `"created_donation"`, `"completed_donation"`, `"cancelled_donation"`. This enables future filtering without schema changes.
- **`title` + `description`**: Pre-rendered at write-time so the Flutter app never needs to compute display strings. This is critical for mobile performance — the client receives display-ready content.
- **`referenceId` + `referenceType`**: Enables deduplication (`referenceId` is unique per `userId + type + action`) and deep-linking (tap an activity → navigate to the donation detail screen).
- **`metadata`**: Denormalized snapshot. Example for a donation: `{ bloodType: "A+", hospitalName: "Cairo Hospital", quantity: 1 }`. This avoids expensive `$lookup`/populate on read queries. The trade-off is slight data redundancy, which is acceptable for a read-heavy timeline.
- **`icon`**: Stored at write-time so the Flutter UI has zero logic to determine icons.

### Indexing Strategy

| Index | Fields | Purpose |
|-------|--------|---------|
| **Primary timeline** | `{ userId: 1, createdAt: -1 }` | Powers the main paginated query — most critical index |
| **Type filter** | `{ userId: 1, type: 1, createdAt: -1 }` | Enables per-category filtering (e.g. "show only donations") |
| **Deduplication** | `{ userId: 1, action: 1, referenceId: 1 }` | Unique compound index with partial filter (`referenceId` is not null) — prevents duplicate activities for the same event |
| **TTL (optional)** | `{ createdAt: 1 }` with `expireAfterSeconds` | Auto-prune activities older than 365 days to bound collection growth |

### Extensibility

New activity types (e.g. `appointment`, `badge_unlock`, `tier_promotion`) are added by:

1. Adding the new value to the `type` enum array
2. Defining new `action` strings (free-form, no enum change needed)
3. Calling `activityService.logActivity()` from the relevant service

No schema migration required. No existing code changes. The `metadata` field (Mixed type) absorbs any type-specific data without schema changes.

---

## 3️⃣ Service Design Plan

### Core Responsibilities

The `activity.service.js` is responsible for:

1. **Creating** activity records (write path)
2. **Querying** the user timeline with pagination and optional type filter (read path)
3. **Deduplication** — ensuring the same event never creates two activities
4. **Dashboard aggregation** — returning the latest N items efficiently

### Required Service Methods

| Method | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `logActivity(userId, payload)` | Core write method. Accepts `{ type, action, title, description, referenceId?, referenceType?, metadata?, icon? }`. Performs deduplication check, then inserts. Fire-and-forget safe (errors are logged, never thrown upstream). |
| `getUserTimeline(userId, filters)` | Core read method. Accepts `{ page, limit, type? }`. Returns `{ activities, pagination }` using the existing `paginationMeta()` utility. |
| `getLatestActivities(userId, count)` | Dashboard shortcut. Returns the latest `count` (default 5) activities with no pagination overhead. Used by `getDashboard` in `donor.controller.js`. |
| `deleteUserActivities(userId)` | GDPR / account deletion support. Bulk-deletes all activities for a user. |

### When Activities Are Created

| Trigger Event | Activity Created |
|---------------|-----------------|
| Donor responds to a request (donation created) | `type: "donation"`, `action: "created_donation"` |
| Donation status changes to `completed` | `type: "donation"`, `action: "completed_donation"` |
| Donation status changes to `cancelled` | `type: "donation"`, `action: "cancelled_donation"` |
| Points awarded (blood donation / emergency / first donation) | `type: "reward"`, `action: "earned_points"` |
| Reward redeemed | `type: "reward"`, `action: "redeemed_reward"` |
| Badge unlocked | `type: "reward"`, `action: "badge_unlocked"` |
| Tier promoted | `type: "reward"`, `action: "tier_promoted"` |
| Donor accepts urgent request | `type: "emergency_response"`, `action: "accepted_urgent_request"` |
| Donor declines urgent request | `type: "emergency_response"`, `action: "declined_urgent_request"` |
| Donor updates profile | `type: "profile_update"`, `action: "updated_profile"` |

### Deduplication Rules

1. Before creating, check for existing activity with the same `userId + action + referenceId`
2. If a matching record exists, skip insertion silently (return null)
3. The unique compound index with `partialFilterExpression` on `referenceId` serves as a database-level safety net (same pattern used by `PointsTransaction.model.js` — proven in this codebase)
4. Activities without a `referenceId` (e.g. `profile_update`) are always inserted (no dedup)

